(1. Theoretical Concepts:) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
11.5 TL
0. g
56.6929133858267775 532.9136220472440755 Td
(How the Button Works: The button closes the circuit between the 5V power source and Pin 2. When pressed,) Tj
T* (the pin reads HIGH. When released, it goes LOW.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Why a Resistor is Needed: A 10k ohm pull-down resistor ensures the Arduino reading defaults cleanly to) Tj
T* (LOW instead of unpredictably 'floating'. Additionally, a 220-330 ohm resistor is necessary before the LED on) Tj
T* (Pin 8 to limit current and prevent drawing too much power, which would burn out the LED.) Tj
ET
